Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.49,0:00:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Many people believe that it doesn’t matter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.32,0:00:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‎which religion you choose,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.45,0:00:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that religions are like different roads that lead
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.99,0:00:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,‎to the same destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.08,0:00:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‎—lasting blessings from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.58,0:00:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‎But can that be true?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.58,0:00:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Does God accept all forms of worship?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.46,0:00:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The Bible itself describes worship as two roads:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.68,0:00:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‎One is spacious \N‎with many people on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.35,0:00:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The other is cramped \N‎with only a few finding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.10,0:00:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Only the cramped road \N‎represents acceptable worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.94,0:00:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,‎leading to life \N‎and blessings from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.23,0:00:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,‎How can we tell if we are on the correct path?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.57,0:00:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Imagine that you’re lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.91,0:00:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‎You stop someone to ask for directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.16,0:01:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‎One person says to head east;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.21,0:01:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‎another says to go west.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.17,0:01:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Finally, someone with a map shows you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.71,0:01:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that the destination is actually north.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.84,0:01:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Which one would you believe?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.51,0:01:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The Bible is like that map,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.52,0:01:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‎leading us to blessings from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.48,0:01:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So why are there so many conflicting beliefs?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.94,0:01:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‎For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.95,0:01:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,‎many religions teach that the human soul
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.74,0:01:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‎lives eternally in a spiritual realm,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.08,0:01:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,‎while others believe that they are reborn
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.75,0:01:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in another body or form.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.42,0:01:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,‎This is just one example
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.13,0:01:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,‎of the many religious beliefs\N‎in conflict with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.55,0:01:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Could all religions \N‎really be teaching the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.81,0:01:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,‎According to the map,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.85,0:02:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,‎the dead know nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.86,0:02:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‎In due time, God will restore them to life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.44,0:02:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and righteous ones will live forever on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.99,0:02:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,‎If the Bible is clear on this teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.08,0:02:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,‎what about other matters, \N‎such as our personal conduct?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.75,0:02:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‎We may belong to a religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.21,0:02:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,‎but if our conduct offends God,\N‎our worship may be futile. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.63,0:02:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The Bible teaches that many people today
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.47,0:02:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‎would be “without self-control,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.80,0:02:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“fierce,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.14,0:02:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‎without love of goodness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.14,0:02:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‎However, it also says
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.60,0:02:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that true worshippers of God\N‎would be peaceable,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.57,0:02:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‎controlling their speech
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.08,0:03:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Rather than saying \N‎there are many religions that please God,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.37,0:03:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‎the Bible says there is only one faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.79,0:03:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‎True worship leads a person
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‎to a good relationship with God
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.96,0:03:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and everlasting life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.92,0:03:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‎You may wonder,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.97,0:03:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‎‘How can I recognize true worship?’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.56,0:03:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,‎That question and others are answered
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.02,0:03:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in lesson 10 of the brochure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.31,0:03:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Good News From God!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.73,0:03:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‎You can download a copy from jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.03,0:03:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Jehovah’s Witnesses \N‎would be happy to study the Bible with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.07,0:03:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Fill in the online request for a Bible study,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.33,0:03:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and a Witness in your area
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.37,0:03:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,‎will call to discuss the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‎at a time and place convenient for you.
